  "message": "Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Recap: 2 blocking items need fixing before consensus",
    "content": "I already sent my full review -- check your earlier messages. Quick recap of the two BLOCKING items:\n\n**B1: Group actions by context headings in the \"All\" view.** US-GTD-3 criterion #3 says \"Default view shows all contexts with context headings.\" The current flat list with per-item context badges does not meet this. When the user sees the \"All\" view, actions should be grouped under context headings (e.g., an `<h2>@home</h2>` followed by the @home actions, then `<h2>@computer</h2>` followed by those actions, etc.). When filtered to a single context, the flat list is fine.\n\n**B2: Wire the live next actions count into the dashboard.** `templates/dashboard.html:20` is hardcoded `<dd>0 items</dd>`. The `count_active_next_actions()` service function exists. Connect them so the dashboard shows the real count.\n\nEverything else looks good from a product perspective. Once these two are fixed, you have my consensus."
  }
}
